  <title>CSS and custom jQuery filter selectors</title>
  <description />
  <content>&lt;p&gt;I’ve discovered a nice set of jQuery filter selectors.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Take this example of selecting the checked radio button in a group&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="./image.axd?picture=image_109.png"&gt;&lt;img style="background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; border-left: 0px; margin: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; display: inline; border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px" title="image" border="0" alt="image" src="./image.axd?picture=image_thumb_109.png" width="244" height="135" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Markup&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="./image.axd?picture=image_110.png"&gt;&lt;img style="background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; border-left: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; display: inline; border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px" title="image" border="0" alt="image" src="./image.axd?picture=image_thumb_110.png" width="564" height="156" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;Script&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;blockquote&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="./image.axd?picture=image_111.png"&gt;&lt;img style="background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; border-left: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; display: inline; border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px" title="image" border="0" alt="image" src="./image.axd?picture=image_thumb_111.png" width="570" height="120" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/blockquote&gt;  &lt;p&gt;There are many many others, e.g. @contains, :disabled, :not(selector), :parent, :password, etc etc, more info in jQuery docs.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
